From Jim De Arras Subject Re My Gun is like my American Express Card In article Jason Kratz U writes In article CSD andy Andy Freeman says I have been at a shooting range where gang members were practicing How do we know that they were gang members and not undercover cops or even law abiding menacing BTW Why the sneer quotes We know because the area that the gun shop shooting range is in is right on the border of the west side of That is a gang infested There are many many bad things going on in that Also I have several friends that live very close to that area who have had problems with some of these By the way where did I say that they were minorities That was what I got from your phrasing Well then were they the ones you saw black You don't deny seem to deny it Do you think that only minorities have gangs Not As far as the quotes are concerned it was totally obvious that they weren't just practicing for I don't know about you but I have never seen anyone else practice marksmanship by taking their gun out of their coat as fast as possible and start That is the recommended way to practice with a CCW Aim alone is no good for defense if you can't get the gun If you would have been there Andy it would've been obvious to you What outside of prejudice would have made it obvious Of course it might not have Who All I do know is that I was there I live here and I know that they were gang When you live here long enough it becomes pretty easy to spot them via gang colors gang signs Yes prejudice is more subtle in the north isn't it One last My sister is a social She makes it her point to find these things out gang signs colors etc because it is in her best interest to do She is nice enough to let me know these things so I can watch out for myself as I live right on the border of the west side of the Enough More than I understand you Jason Jim I'm always rethinking There's never been a day when I haven't rethought But I can't do that by Bill Clinton April If I were an American as I am an Englishman while a foreign troop was landed in my country I never would lay down my arms never never never WILLIAM PITT EARL OF CHATHAM